A forest can regrow after a fire but it takes a lot of time and energy. It's a lot easier to MAINTAIN your web3 reputation than to REBUILD it after a dumpster fire. Put out fires early and own your mistakes. How we do it really matters. The Blockchain doesn't lie. BUILD.

No one is perfect and we all make mistakes. The reality of a digital world is that those mistakes are often on public display. How we handle them says a lot about who we are and the record of HOW we handle mistakes can strengthen or weaken our permanent web3 reputation.
